For 7th Thats the hard part to write. Tommy looked me in the eye and kept it straight. I deeply appreciate his support. I got to give my fitness a chance. Its not a lack of competing or effort or desire. Right now, as I prep to advance through rounds, its about execution and trust in the calculated risk. In hindsight, todays 51.9 is a great first lap. But I got sleepy - I had the eyes down while the pack I can race with (1:.6) moved away. I had a great finish in the last 100m but again, I got to give my fitness a chance - Be there at 600m. The guys I get to race now are too good - Olympians. Theyre not coming back to me. I need to give myself a chance to fight, not fight back. I felt so in control after the race . Finding the good in my fourth 1:46 of the year - very consistent and progressing well. Excited to embrace the challenge of maintaining a level head and not thinking less of myself, but thinking of myself less. pretty happy with this opener. had no idea how a 3k was gonna feel but thought I could run 7:45 going in. got through 2k in 5:17 feeling really comfortable and just started working it down from there. 2:30 last K was solid but only 59 for the last 400. definitely a faster time in me with some more competition. feeling super fit and ready for a mile.
couldve been better, couldve been worse but pretty happy with the time off the double. just got out a bit too slow and hard to make moves in an 800m. felt pretty smooth throughout though

more good progress but still putting all the pieces together. got out pretty poorly and worked a little hard to move up but put together a good kick still. hopefully fast enough for a nationals qualifier.

3rd in 7:54. ran it 2 and a half hours after the mile and wasnt sure how i was gonna feel but found a bit left in the tank at the end. didnt have any expectations coming in so just a nice bonus and a good validation of the fitness being there right now.

2nd in 3:56.1. happy with the race overall, parker ran it pretty perfectly and was just too far behind when he started to move. wish i positioned myself better earlier but feel pretty good about how i ran overall.

felt pretty good coming around the curve and was hoping to make a good push but ate shit in the last 70m lol. rough way for it to end but walking away from the meet and from indoor season feeling pretty confident knowing i can hang with the best guys in the country. excited to get going outdoors

mixed feelings but coming away feeling mostly really positive about this one. I thought winning my heat would be closer to 3:35 so definitely wanted to run faster but also really happy with how patient I stayed and how I ran it. felt like I had so much left in the last 150 meters and was able to pull away for the heat win. ready for another 1500 to hopefully shave a few seconds off.

1:47.46. Bit of a PR and a heat win. Went to the back and got out in 53 low but was hoping for 52 mid. Started to move up on the back stretch and saved something for the last 80. Felt really good and nice to see some speed still here
heat caught up to me on the last few miles

2nd place, 2nd in NCAA history, 4th in world history. 3:55.2 split. Got the baton on pace for sub 16 and wasnt gonna slow it down.
